{
  "id": "waste-notes-brings-n",
  "slug": "brings",
  "type": "annotation",
  "title": "brings the sailor",
  "sourceFile": "Waste_notes/brings_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>brings\n        the sailor ...</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>This may not appear as exact as Sappho's lines, but I\n        had in mind the 'longshore' or 'dory' fisherman, who\n        returns at nightfall. [Eliot's note] Sappho's poem\n        addressed Hesperus, the evening star, as the star that\n        brings everyone home from work to evening rest; her poem\n        is here distorted by Eliot. There is also an echo of\n        Robert Louis Stevenson's Requiem: \"Home is the\n        sailor, home from sea\". (NA)</p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font>link one</font></td>\n<td><a href=\"publication_data.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>link two</td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "brings the sailor ... This may not appear as exact as Sappho's lines, but I had in mind the 'longshore' or 'dory' fisherman, who returns at nightfall. [Eliot's note] Sappho's poem addressed Hesperus, the evening star, as the star that brings everyone home from work to evening rest; her poem is here distorted by Eliot. There is also an echo of Robert Louis Stevenson's Requiem: \"Home is the sailor, home from sea\". (NA) reference topics link one link two back to \"The Waste Land\"",
